	<tr><td>new probe, x10<br/><br/>The voltage here shows less overshoot, down to -1.8V. But the flanks are much higher here, due to the higher bandwidth for the harmonics. The high voltage does not show much overshoot anymore, but also is max'd at about 4V.</td><td><a href="imgs/10MHz_x10_NewProbe.png"><img width="300px" src="imgs/10MHz_x10_NewProbe.png"/></a></td></tr>
	<tr><td>old probe, x10<br/><br/>The old probe again only shows slightly higher overshoot, but otherwise looks very similar to the new probe.</td><td><a href="imgs/10MHz_x10_OldProbe.png"><img width="300px" src="imgs/10MHz_x10_OldProbe.png"/></a></td></tr>
